<div id="T8Writer_Overlay">
	<div id="T8Writer_Container">
		<h2 id="T8Writer_Title" style="opacity: 1;">Welcome to T8Writer</h2>
		<form id="T8Writer_Form">
			<ul id="T8Writer_Documents" style="opacity: 1;" tabindex="2"></ul>
			<div id="T8Writer_Contents" contenteditable="true" tabindex="1">&#8204</div>
			<p id="T8Writer_Messages" style="opacity: 1;"></p>
			<div id="T8Writer_Controls" style="opacity: 1;">
				<h3>Current document:</h3>
				<button id="T8Writer_Save">Save</button>
				<button id="T8Writer_Revert">Revert</button>
				<button id="T8Writer_Email" class="disabled">Email</button>

				<h3>New document:</h3>
				<button id="T8Writer_Create">Create</button>
				
				<h3>T8Writer:</h3>
				<button id="T8Writer_Help" class="disabled">Help</button>
			</div>
		</form>
		<form id="T8Writer_NewDocument" action="#new">
			<label for="T8Writer_NewDocTitle">What would you like to name your document?</label>
			<input id="T8Writer_NewDocTitle" type="text" value="Untitled 1"/>
			<button id="T8Writer_SubmitTitle" type="submit">Save</button>
		</form>
		<form id="T8Writer_Command" action="#new">
			<label for="T8Writer_CommandPrompt">Type your command and hit enter</label>
			<input id="T8Writer_CommandPrompt" type="text" value=""/>
		</form>
		<a id="exitT8Writer" href="#save_and_exit" title="Save and exit T8Writer">x</a>
	</div>
	<div id="T8Writer_HelpInfo">
		<h3>Getting started with T8Writer</h3>
		<h4>Creating your first document:</h4>
		<p>
			To create your first document, simply click inside the blank text area
			or click on the &ldquo;Create&rdquo; button in the lower right. You&rsquo;ll
			be prompted to enter the title of your new document. Just type it in and click
			&ldquo;Submit&rdquo;. The title, which will appear above the text field is editable.
			Just click on it to edit it at any time.
		</p>
		<h3>The command line</h3>
		<p>
			T8writer is all about flow. Since you&rsquo;ll spend most of your time typing, T8Writer
			gives you commands you can type, like &ldquo;save&rdquo;, &ldquo;exit&rdquo;, and &ldquo;revert&rdquo;.
		</p>
		<p>
			To activate the command line, type <kbd>alt</kbd> + <kbd>.</kbd>; then, type your command and hit <kbd>enter</kbd>.
		</p>
		<ul>
			<li></li>
		</ul>
	</div>
</div>